The paper discusses a less greedy algorithm for sparse signal reconstruction in compressive sensing, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also analyzes the performance of the algorithm using coherence indices, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of the algorithm, which is relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.SP, followed by cs.LG, cs.NA, and cs.SY.
